<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="part" searchtype="LEGISLATION PART" subdoc="false" toc-caption="PART III PARTIES [rr 15&#x2013;17]">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="PART-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT3" type="ext"/>PART III</designum></desig><title searchtype="PART-TITLE">PARTIES [rr 15&#x2013;17]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R15"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,220] r 15 Actions in rem: parties">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R15" type="ext"/>[255,220]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Actions <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>: parties</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>15</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R15.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R15.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Initiating process in a proceeding commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph> must specify a relevant person in relation to the maritime claim concerned as a defendant.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R15.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R15.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A relevant person may be specified by reference to ownership of, or other relevant relationship with, the ship or other property concerned.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R16"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,225] r 16 Actions in rem: ship or property">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R16" type="ext"/>[255,225]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Actions <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>: ship or property</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>16</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R16.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R16.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Initiating process in a proceeding commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph> must identify the ship or other property concerned in relation to the maritime claim.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R16.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R16.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If the proceeding is commenced against a surrogate ship, the ship in relation to which it is a surrogate must also be identified in the initiating process.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R16.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R16.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Initiating process may identify more than 1 ship as a surrogate ship.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,230] r 17 Amendment of process">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17" type="ext"/>[255,230]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Amendment of process</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>17</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The powers of a court in relation to amendment of process and joinder of parties extend to making an order, on such terms as are just:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>substituting for a defendant identified in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R15.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subrule 15(2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 another person; and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>substituting for a ship another ship.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If process in a proceeding is amended by substituting for a ship another ship, the proceeding is taken to have been commenced against the other ship at the time specified in the order or, if no time is so specified, at the time when the order was made.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37 and 1.38, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255230-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,230.5]">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [255,230.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(CTH) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005X" refpt="CTH_REG_1988-269" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Admiralty Rules 1988</remotelink> r 17(2).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255230-5" type="ext"/>[255,230.5] </edpnum></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R17.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">rule 17(2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, the court has a discretion whether to order that the proceedings against the substituted ship shall be taken to have commenced at the time of the original proceedings. This is particularly important when, at the time the amendment is sought the time limit in relation to the original cause of action has expired or the ship to be added is now under different ownership: see ALRC Report No 33 <emph typestyle="it">Civil Admiralty Jurisdiction</emph>, 1986, para 215.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level></leg:levelbody></leg:level-vrnt></leg:level></leg:body></LEGDOC>